Validate must reject duplicate spec IDs, duplicate marker IDs, edges referencing unknown endpoints, self-edges, duplicate edges, directed cycles among spec-spec edges, resolutions referencing unknown endpoints, resolutions on node pairs with no declared edge, or duplicate resolutions. Edges whose endpoint does not exist (broken edges — typically a typo in a &lt;ref&gt; target) are NOT rejected here; they surface as TodoBrokenEdge drift items so the user can fix the spec text or restore the missing spec. Validation must pass when all references are consistent. See principles.specs_are_truth.